  "text": "lium to collect ASL results in a significant hydrostatic pressure gradient, which has been reported to disturb the barrier function of the epithelium and result in a large flow of subepithelial (i.e., interstitial) liquid to the epithelial cell surface [CITATION_1] . Because of our use of the narrow-bore tubing and the extended length of time that was necessary to collect this liquid, we are confident that our results reflect the composition of ASL rather than that of other liquid compartments.",
